SIMPLE: refusal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Refusal
<hw>Re*fus"al</hw> <pr>(-<it>a</it>l)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of refusing; denial of anything demanded, solicited, or
offered for acceptance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Do they not seek occasion of new quarrels,⟦br⟧
On my <qex>refusal</qex>, to distress me more?</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The right of taking in preference to others; the
choice of taking or refusing; option; <as>as, to give one the
<ex>refusal</ex> of a farm; to have the <ex>refusal</ex> of an
employment</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Refuse</ent>⟦br⟧
